commit_list.message:
html_safe the default options Strings

This gem broke while playing with:
    - rails ~>3.2
    - simple_form ~>2.0

The <option> tags are all unsafe and escaped, this is a simple enough fix
for that.

Bootstrap an EventSource based remote API

When starting slide-em-up, export APIKEY=somevalue to setup your
"control" channel. The APIKEY then allows you ton control your slides.

 * The Event-Source channel is available publicly through the rollowing
   path: /remote/whatever/events

 * Send GET requests to /remote/:apikey/:action to send :action through
   the Event source channel.

A Basic example is included in slideshow.js which reacts to 'next' and
'prev' messages to move through your deck.

Add hash command to CLI

Add another CLI option to show OSDB hash for a given file:
osdb hash /path/to/somefile

Use HTTPS and cleanup API style

OSDB was initially not available over HTTPS, which was bad but they
fixed that recently. Now you can grab subtitles and leak a little less
information on what you're watching.

The "cleanup" of the API consists of the following:

 - Rename some methods related to IMDB,
 - Use go style attributes ("ID" instead of "id"),
 - Use go style variable case ("fooBar" instead of "foo_bar").

This is a breaking change, especially if you used IMDB methods but it
does not affect you as long as you use to the 0.2 release.

Merge pull request #3 from DexterLB/tests_and_encodings

Implement character encoding support and write some live tests
Update Travis-CI config to test w/ Go 1.5 & 1.6

Merge pull request #2 from DexterLB/checkmoviehash

Implement CheckMovieHash

Merge pull request #1 from gregdel/fixTypeMismatch

Fix invalid condition check in SearchSubtitles

Use OSDB_LANG env var as default for --lang

This is a CLI related commit: we now allow you to add more clutter to
your shell environment vars by introducing the OSDB_LANG variable. The
CLI program will use it as a default value for the --lang flag.

Feel free to save yourself some typing.

I also golint-ed the OSDB program, which still needs some love.

Vendor dependencies

Go's recent 1.5 release shipped with experimental support for vendoring
dependencies. Let's play with that a little. :)

This is completely optional, and transparent. To build from source using
vendored libs, use: "GO15VENDOREXPERIMENT=1 go build ./...". Simply
remove the env. variable to keep the traditional behaviour.

Update IMDB cmd

 - Working "show" command (hi docopt!).
 - Format "search" to display movie ID first.

Add support for several languages to "osdb get"

When getting subtitles from CLI, allow the use of several languages by
using the "--lang" flag with a comma-separated list of languages:

The command "osdb get --lang fra,eng sample.video" will try to find
french subtitles first, and fallback to english if none are found.
Link to travis build in README
Update test user-agent string until 0.1 release

Cleaning Subtitle stype

Subtitle.toUploadParams does less, and does not include the client's
Token automatically – which allows us to remove the only parameter to
this method.

TryUploadSubtitle now ignores the <data> returned by OSDB: because we
need to be able to map a concrete type to the value, but the server
insists on returning either <array> of structs, or plain <struct>s under
the same name.

One way to solve this second problem would be a two-pass decoding... :fearful:
Allow OSDB_SERVER env var to change remote server
Not finding subtitles is not an error

OSDB returns different types sometimes

When searching subtitles, OSDB's XMLRPC response is not always of the
same type, for example when you search for a file hash:
  - if it matches anything, we get an array of subtitle structures,
  - if it does not, we get a boolean set to false.

One way of handling this is to use a interface{} and inspect the pointed
values to determine how to cast them. Or we could just look at the error
code and do something hackish when it points to a type error... :/
This things has almost no tests ;_;
Make "osdb imdb" eat up all its arguments

Add "osdb put" command

For now, it does not upload anything, but rather tries to upload
subtitles, checking with OSDB whether they already have those...

Fix methods to try subtitle upload

Fix `HasSubtitles`, because it did not work, and sent messed up XML-RPC
parameters to TryUploadSubtitles.

Also, add `HasSubtitlesForFiles(movie, subs)` to easily build up the
required Subtitle type that `HasSubtitles` expect.
Build Subtitle{} by inspecting movie & sub files

Use ENV vars to login with CLI helper

 - OSDB_LOGIN
 - OSDB_PASSWORD
 - OSDB_LANG
Playing with TabWriter to display movie details

Add a very simple "osdb" command

This is mostly to test the lib, and try to clean up some of the current
code w/ a "real-world" application.

Signed-off-by: Arnaud Berthomier <oz@cyprio.net>

Use slice type aliases instead of slices

 - Alias Subtitles ([]Subtitle), and Movies ([]Movies).
 - Add Best() method to Subtitles() which pick the best subtitle
   out of a collection.
GH now supports todo-items in README.md
Check server status when getting subtitles

Add IMDB movie and subtitles search

 - Search movies on IMDB,
 - and search subtitles by IMDB ID.

Add HashFile method

Move most of the Hash(path string) code to HashFile. This should allow
al little more flexibility in the API: providing only a string-based
method to deal with paths is not very nice IMHO.
Check lists are only for PR -_-

Use a map[string]string in hasSubtitleParams

Following the recent updates in kolo/xmlrpc

Add a few words on HasSubtitles

OSDb's method for this is actually named TryUploadSubtitles, although it
does not require any form of file upload. It *is* a little weird.

I haven't looked into it too much yet. However, I am thinking that the
XML field names we send here *are* case-sensitive because the API always
replies with a "false", when checking wheteher a freshly found subtitle
already exists...

Which would mean that queries parameter names are all lowercased (per
the docs), but that, for server replies, the same fields are camel-case.
Well done! :sob:
Use a slice param for HasSubtitles
Set Client's xmlrpc.Client property on initialize

Refactor to a client-based API

- Add an osdb.Client type, rather than ugly globals.
- Separate different concerns in different files (rpc client, subtitles, ...).
- Update README.
Move anonymous Token-getter to a private method
Use OSDB test agent by default

Use kolo/xmlrpc rather than mattn/go-xmlrpc

The latter has some bugs, and the former makes better use of Golang's
net/rpc package... So be it.

Add basic osdb.SearchForFile

Update Travis CI: run tests with Go 1.8 only

Use Golang's dep tool

dep is still alpha software, so it will break in the future. It looks
like the community wants to make this the reference, so let's go for it.
